    <title> Vegetarian Rice </title>
  </head>
  <body>
	<h1> Vegetarian Rice </h1>
	<img src="Vegetarian Rice.jpg" alt="Vegetarian Rice">
	<h2> Ingredients </h2>
<ul>
	<li> <p>1/2 chopped onion </p> </li>
	<li> <p>1 chopped garlic clove </p> </li>
	<li> <p>1 chopped courgette </p> </li>
	<li> <p>1 grated carrot </p> </li>
	<li> <p>1 chopped red or yellow pepper</p> </li>
  <li> <p>75g frozen peas </p> </li>
  <li> <p>1/2 tin of chopped tomatoes </p> </li>
  <li> <p>350ml Vegetable stock</p> </li>
  <li> <p>150g Dried brown rice</p> </li>
  <li> <p>1 tbsp of dried parsley</p> </li>
  <li> <p>1 tsp Turmeric</p> </li>
  <li> <p>Seasoning</p> </li>
</ul>

	<h2> Method </h2>
<ol>
	<li> <p>Add onion, garlic, and turmeric to the pan with a splash of veg stock.</p> </li>
	<li> <p>Stirring, cook gently for 3 mins. Then, add the chopped courgette, grated carrot, and chopped pepper.</p> </li>
	<li> <p>Stir well for a further 3 mins, then add the dried rice. </p> </li>
	<li> <p>Stir the rice well with the vegetables.</p> </li>
	<li> <p>Once rice is distributed well throughout the mixture. Add the stock-leave to boil. </p> </li>	
  <li> <p>Once boiled, immediately turn the heat down to simmer and cover. Cook for 10 mins.</p> </li>
  <li> <p>Add in chopped tomatoes and frozen peas and stir. </p> </li>
  <li> <p>Cover and simmer for a further 10 mins</p> </li>
  <li> <p>Once cooked, stir in dried parsley with seasoning</p> </li>
  <li> <p>Spoon rice into two dishes.</p> </li>
</ol>
  </body>
</html>
